34:36.491 --> 34:41.031
That investigation has involved
34 FBI employees

34:41.161 --> 34:42.822
at a cost of $16 million--

34:42.956 --> 34:45.493
-Where did you get this information?
-An FOIA request.

34:45.625 --> 34:48.242
If it's inaccurate,
we're happy to amend the record.

34:48.378 --> 34:50.995
-Your statement is now concluded.
-Almost. Almost.

34:51.130 --> 34:54.293
At the inception of this investigation,

34:54.426 --> 34:57.794
Director Foerstel formed
an exploratory committee for a senate bid.

34:57.929 --> 34:58.885
Turn the recorder off.

34:59.014 --> 35:02.097
He also formed
a political action committee.

35:02.225 --> 35:04.091
You heard me. Turn it off!

35:10.817 --> 35:13.024
-Hey.
-Hey. [sighs]

35:13.778 --> 35:15.689
We got the plates back
from the suspect's car,

35:15.822 --> 35:17.483
the guy who met with Damian.

35:18.491 --> 35:20.357
Why didn't Chuck
just give me this directly?

35:20.493 --> 35:23.736
He thought it best you hear it from me.
He was right.

35:23.872 --> 35:26.614
The car comes back to the Russian embassy.

35:26.750 --> 35:30.709
<i>The driver was Oleg Pushkin.
He's an attache there. He's also FSB.</i>

35:30.837 --> 35:34.000
And it's not the first time
he's met with Damian.

35:34.132 --> 35:35.918
| think you know where I'm going with this.

35:36.051 --> 35:37.507
Damian is MI6.

35:37.636 --> 35:39.092
Yes. He may have turned.

35:39.721 --> 35:42.304
We never found a connection
between Patrick Lloyd and Russia.

35:42.432 --> 35:44.890
Meaning whatever interest
Russia could have

35:45.018 --> 35:48.261
in thwarting the Icarus investigation
that Lloyd started is a mystery.

35:48.396 --> 35:50.888
Maybe Russia's just taking advantage
of the situation.

35:51.024 --> 35:53.436
Destabilize our government
by making us chase our tail.

35:53.568 --> 35:55.525
Or maybe we're missing something.

35:55.654 --> 35:57.270
No, maybe I miss something.

35:57.405 --> 35:59.362
I'm gonna bring Damian in and find out.

35:59.491 --> 36:00.652
Hannah...

36:01.326 --> 36:05.490
if this guy is who we think he is,
he's beyond dangerous.

36:05.622 --> 36:06.862
That may be true, Aaron,

36:06.998 --> 36:09.080
but no one is more dangerous
than I am right now.

36:09.209 --> 36:11.416
This is my mess.
| will clean it up.

36:11.544 --> 36:13.626
All right.
Put your team together.

36:20.428 --> 36:22.385
[bell tolling]

36:41.533 --> 36:43.900
So what is this big surprise?

36:45.620 --> 36:46.451
That I know.

36:47.872 --> 36:49.124
Know what?

36:49.791 --> 36:51.077
About the warehouse fire.

36:51.876 --> 36:54.743
Alfonso Lang. Oleg Pushkin.

36:54.879 --> 36:57.541
- I don't understand.
-Yes, you do.

36:59.634 --> 37:00.715
Okay.

37:01.386 --> 37:05.004
Let's start from the top.
| saved you from that warehouse fire.

37:05.140 --> 37:06.801
After you set it.

37:07.976 --> 37:12.186
| trusted you. I really trusted you,
and you lied to me about everything.

37:12.313 --> 37:13.565
| didn't lie.

37:13.690 --> 37:14.680
Turn around.

37:15.608 --> 37:19.693
Middle of a bridge. That's smart.

37:19.821 --> 37:23.155
-Nowhere for me to go, right?
-I know where you're going.

37:23.283 --> 37:25.194
-You're gonna be there a long time.
-Hannah.

37:25.326 --> 37:27.317
Turn around
and put your hands on your head.

37:28.163 --> 37:31.451
| need to show you something.
It'll explain everything.

37:31.583 --> 37:34.416
| just need to reach into my pocket, okay?

37:34.544 --> 37:36.876
-You reach for anything, you're dead.
- I have to, Hannah.

37:37.756 --> 37:38.917
Damian.

38:23.134 --> 38:25.216
[baby cooing]

38:33.728 --> 38:36.846
Hello, Tom Kirkman's voicemail.

38:37.565 --> 38:39.602
This is Tom Kirkman's wife,

38:39.734 --> 38:44.570
who is no longer the subject or target
of a federal investigation.

38:45.824 --> 38:47.861
| beat it.

38:47.992 --> 38:49.244
We beat it.

38:50.036 --> 38:54.496
And the only thing I wanna say to you
is I love you.

38:55.500 --> 38:56.706
[sighs]

